(6, 'Prof. (Mrs) Maame Afua Nkrumah', 'Takoradi Technical University, Takoradi. Ghana.', '', '7137117.jpg', '&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Prof.\r\n(Mrs.) Maame Afua Nkrumah was born in April, 1975 in the Central Region of\r\nGhana. She is an Associate Professor at the Centre for Languages and Liberal\r\nStudies (CELLIBS), Takoradi Technical University (TTU) and is currently the\r\nDean of International Programmes and External Linkages Office (IPELO).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Prof.\r\n(Mrs.) Nkrumah is a full-time lecturer at Takoradi Technical University and a\r\npart-time lecturer at the Ghana Telecom University.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Her\r\nareas of specialisation are Educational Quality Assurance and Educational\r\nManagement, Assessment and Evaluation. She holds a PhD in Education and a\r\nPost-Graduate Certificate in Research Methods from the University of Bristol,\r\nUnited Kingdom. She obtained her Masters Degree in Educational Management\r\nAssessment and Evaluation from the University of Twente in The Netherlands and\r\nher Bachelor of Science Education from the University of Cape Coast (UCC),\r\nGhana. She is a teacher by profession and was trained at the OLA Training\r\nCollege, Cape Coast. She has taught at both the basic and secondary school\r\nlevels in Ghana. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Prof. (Mrs.) Nkrumah obtained her Junior Secondary School\r\ncertificate at the Sekondi-Takoradi Metropolitan Assembly (STMA) Junior\r\nSecondary School in Takoradi and her Senior Secondary education at Fijai\r\nSecondary School, Sekondi, Ghana.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Among\r\nthe many departments/units within TTU that she has headed are: The Examinations\r\nUnit, The Academic Quality Assurance Unit and The Centre for Languages and\r\nLiberal Studies. She has, additionally, been a member of some high-profile\r\ncommittees and boards including: The Executive Committee, The Planning and\r\nResource Committee, The Business Development Board and The Academic Board of\r\nTTU. Prof. Nkrumah has also chaired a number of Committees and Boards, with the\r\nrecent ones being The Library and The Publications Boards respectively. She a\r\nnumber of peer reviewed publications in both local and international refereed\r\njournals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;She has attended and presented papers at both local and international\r\nconferences. Her research interest is in educational quality assurance and\r\ninstitutional effectiveness using both qualitative and quantitative (e.g.\r\nmultilevel modelling) approaches.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Prof.\r\n(Mrs.) Maame Afua Nkrumah has obtained training in the following areas: How to\r\nSurvive as A Scientist in The Higher Education Environment (by DAAD), How to\r\nManage International Offices (Universities of Cape Coast and University of\r\nMines and Technology), How to Publish (Elsevier Publish Campus Author\r\nWorkshop), Assessment of Competency Based Training (National Board for\r\nProfessional and Technical Education) and Improving Management and Leadership\r\nCapacity Programmes (NPT/UCC).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;She\r\nhas further been involved in the management of a number of projects, both at\r\nthe local and international levels. For example, she is a project member for\r\nthe Establishment of a Renewable Energy Education Framework (REEF) –\r\nAcross-universities in Ghana for a sustainable curriculum focus (2020-2023)\r\nbetween Hochschule Düsseldorf (HSD) of Germany and the following five Ghanaian\r\nuniversities: Cape Coast Technical University (CCTU), Koforidua Technical\r\nUniversity (KTU), University of Cape Coast (UCC), Takoradi Technical University\r\n(TTU) and also Renewable Energy Association of Ghana (REAG). &amp;nbsp;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;serif&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;Prof.\r\nNkrumah is the Project coordinator for TTU for the following projects: Erasmus\r\nmobility for learners and staff – higher education students and staff mobility\r\nbetween Hochschule Düsseldorf – University of Applied Sciences, Germany and\r\nTakoradi Technical University, Ghana (2019/20-2021/22 Academic years); Erasmus\r\nMobility for learners and staff – higher education students and staff mobility\r\nbetween Eszterhazy Karoly University, Hungary (2019/20-2021/22 academic years)\r\nand Takoradi Technical University, Ghana (2019/20-2021/22 Academic years); International\r\nexchange programme between Institute National Polytechnique Felix\r\nHouphoinet-Boigny (Inp- Hb) Ivory Coast, and Takoradi Takoradi Technical\r\nUniversity (TTU), Ghana; Erasmus Mobility for learners and staff – higher\r\neducation students and staff mobility between Str. Universității 1Oradea,\r\nRomania (2019/20-2022/3 academic years) and Takoradi Technical University,\r\nGhana (2019/20-2021/22 Academic years); Siemens - Takoradi Technical University\r\nPartnership; Ecole Nationale d’Ingénieurs de Tarbes (ENIT) and TTU Partnership;\r\nand University of Auburn, USA and Takoradi Technical University\r\nEntrepreneurship project.&amp;nbsp;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 'Keynote Speaker', 1);

